==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cist
<hw>Cist</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>cista</ets> box,
chest, Gr. <?/ Cf. <er>Chest</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Antiq.)</fld> <def>A box or chest. Specifically:
<sd>(a)</sd> A bronze receptacle, round or oval, frequently decorated
with engravings on the sides and cover, and with feet, handles, etc., of
decorative castings. <sd>(b)</sd> A cinerary urn. See
<xex>Illustration</xex> in Appendix.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>See <er>Cyst</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cisted</ent>⟦br⟧
